<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Word2vec - Tag - KK's Blog (fromkk)</title><link>https://fromkk.com/tags/word2vec/</link><description>fromkk.com is my personal blog, Explore insightful posts on Python, machine learning, and other stuff. keyword: python, machine learning, programming</description><generator>Hugo 0.164.0 &amp; FixIt v0.4.5</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Sun, 10 Aug 2025 18:44:05 +0800</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://fromkk.com/tags/word2vec/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Models and Architectures in Word2vec</title><link>https://fromkk.com/posts/models-and-architechtures-in-word2vec/</link><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jan 2018 15:14:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://fromkk.com/posts/models-and-architechtures-in-word2vec/</guid><category domain="https://fromkk.com/categories/machine-learning/">Machine-Learning</category><description>&lt;p&gt;Generally, &lt;code&gt;word2vec&lt;/code&gt; is a language model to predict the words probability based on the context. When build the model, it create word embedding for each word, and word embedding is widely used in many NLP tasks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 class="heading-element" id="models"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Models&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a href="#models" class="heading-mark"&gt;
 &lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path d="m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 class="heading-element" id="cbow--continuous-bag-of-words"&gt;&lt;span&gt;CBOW (Continuous Bag of Words)&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a href="#cbow--continuous-bag-of-words" class="heading-mark"&gt;
 &lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path d="m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Use the context to predict the probability of current word. (In the picture, the word is encoded with one-hot encoding, &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;span class="katex-mathml"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;W&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;_&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;V&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mstyle mathcolor="#ff4949"&gt;&lt;mtext&gt;\*&lt;/mtext&gt;&lt;/mstyle&gt;&lt;mi&gt;N&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;W\_{V\*N}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;span class="base"&gt;&lt;span class="strut" style="height:1.06em;vertical-align:-0.31em;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right:0.13889em;"&gt;W&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="mord" style="margin-right:0.02778em;"&gt;_&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="mord"&gt;&lt;span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right:0.22222em;"&gt;V&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="mord text" style="color:#ff4949;"&gt;&lt;span class="mord" style="color:#ff4949;"&gt;\*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right:0.10903em;"&gt;N&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; is word embedding, and &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;span class="katex-mathml"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;W&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mi mathvariant="normal"&gt;_&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;V&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mstyle mathcolor="#ff4949"&gt;&lt;mtext&gt;\*&lt;/mtext&gt;&lt;/mstyle&gt;&lt;mi&gt;N&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;msup&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;mo mathvariant="normal" lspace="0em" rspace="0em"&gt;′&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/msup&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;W\_{V\*N}^{&amp;#x27;}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;span class="base"&gt;&lt;span class="strut" style="height:1.3924em;vertical-align:-0.31em;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right:0.13889em;"&gt;W&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="mord" style="margin-right:0.02778em;"&gt;_&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="mord"&gt;&lt;span class="mord"&gt;&lt;span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right:0.22222em;"&gt;V&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="mord text" style="color:#ff4949;"&gt;&lt;span class="mord" style="color:#ff4949;"&gt;\*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right:0.10903em;"&gt;N&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="msupsub"&gt;&lt;span class="vlist-t"&gt;&lt;span class="vlist-r"&gt;&lt;span class="vlist" style="height:1.0824em;"&gt;&lt;span style="top:-3.0824em;margin-right:0.05em;"&gt;&lt;span class="pstrut" style="height:2.5795em;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight"&gt;&lt;span class="mord mtight"&gt;&lt;span class="mord mtight"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="msupsub"&gt;&lt;span class="vlist-t"&gt;&lt;span class="vlist-r"&gt;&lt;span class="vlist" style="height:0.8278em;"&gt;&lt;span style="top:-2.931em;margin-right:0.0714em;"&gt;&lt;span class="pstrut" style="height:2.5em;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="sizing reset-size3 size1 mtight"&gt;&lt;span class="mord mtight"&gt;&lt;span class="mord mtight"&gt;′&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, the output weight matrix in hidden layer, is same as &lt;span class="katex"&gt;&lt;span class="katex-mathml"&gt;&lt;math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mover accent="true"&gt;&lt;mi&gt;υ&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;mo&gt;^&lt;/mo&gt;&lt;/mover&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding="application/x-tex"&gt;\hat{\upsilon}&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="katex-html" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;span class="base"&gt;&lt;span class="strut" style="height:0.6944em;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="mord accent"&gt;&lt;span class="vlist-t"&gt;&lt;span class="vlist-r"&gt;&lt;span class="vlist" style="height:0.6944em;"&gt;&lt;span style="top:-3em;"&gt;&lt;span class="pstrut" style="height:3em;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="mord mathnormal" style="margin-right:0.03588em;"&gt;υ&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="top:-3em;"&gt;&lt;span class="pstrut" style="height:3em;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="accent-body" style="left:-0.2222em;"&gt;&lt;span class="mord"&gt;^&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; in following equations)&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Parameters in doc2vec</title><link>https://fromkk.com/posts/parameters-in-dov2vec/</link><pubDate>Thu, 03 Aug 2017 15:20:00 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://fromkk.com/posts/parameters-in-dov2vec/</guid><category domain="https://fromkk.com/categories/machine-learning/">Machine-Learning</category><description>&lt;p&gt;Here are some parameter in &lt;code&gt;gensim&lt;/code&gt;&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;doc2vec&lt;/code&gt; class.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 class="heading-element" id="window"&gt;&lt;span&gt;window&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a href="#window" class="heading-mark"&gt;
 &lt;svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path d="m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z"&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
 &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;window is the maximum distance between the predicted word and context words used for prediction within a document. It will look behind and ahead.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>